  "time_ut": 1658744846,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 01 \u0daf\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0d85\u0d82\u0d9a \u0dad\u0dc4\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2 - \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8 QR \u0d9b\u0dda\u0dad\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vehicle number plate system ends on 01 August - after that, fueling will go to QR station",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Electricity and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that from August 1st, the system of issuing fuel according to the last number of the number plate will end and after that the fuel will be issued according to the National Fuel License. The minister has announced this in a tweet.",
        "Also, from tomorrow (26th) CEYPETCO and LIOC fuel stations across the island will issue fuel according to the National Fuel License (QR) system.",
        "1. The National Fuel License (QR) will be implemented from Tuesday 26th July at several CEYPETCO and LIOC petrol stations across the country. This system will be in effect till August 1 with the last digits of the number plate.",
        "2. Locations with no facilities or technical difficulties will follow the final figure and fuel quota allocation until the technical issues are resolved. 60% of the stations have already been tested with equipment and will be given priority in fuel delivery.",
        "3. All petrol station owners of CEYPETCO and LIOC are requested to adopt QR system immediately and distribution to QR-enabled petrol stations will be strictly enforced by 1st August. We appeal to the public to register with the National Fuel License and support the initiative.",
        "4. Users and government agencies will be given options to register multiple vehicles with their business registration by the end of this week. Divisional secretaries will be given access to the system to register generators, gardening equipment and other equipment.",
        "5. The Police Department and Divisional Secretaries will be given access to register three-wheelers, and each three-wheeler will be allocated to a specific fuel station. Accordingly, the Ministry of Transport will be given access to register buses to depots or petrol stations.",
        "6. Other services like health, agriculture, fisheries, tourism, industries and service providing sectors will be given access to the system to register their needs and reserve vehicles at petrol stations.",
        "7. From 1st August only QR system quota will be in effect and last number of number plate system and other provisions will not be valid. National Youth Corps and National Youth Council members and volunteers to support the program at petrol stations for the next 10 days."
      ],
